      "citation_id": "[CITATION_2]",
      "span_text": "The etiology of poststroke depression (PSD) is thought to be multifactorial, involving psychosocial and biological mechanisms."
    },
    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_3]",
      "span_text": "The SERT protein is localized on the presynaptic membrane of serotonergic neurons, where it controls the intensity and duration of serotonergic signaling through reuptake of the neurotransmitter into the synapse. Because SERT is the target of selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors, variations in the SERT gene have been widely studied as possible risk factors for psychiatric illness."
